AB  - This paper proposes a new performance index referred to as the Nth-order Omega that includes the well-known Omega as a special case. The index is established by adopting an approach that is free of a utility functional form or/and distributional assumptions. A decision-theoretic foundation for our index is further established through introducing a new distribution ranking criterion. The index is monotonic with respect to Nth-degree stochastic dominance and offers a complete ordering on gambles. An empirical example of deriving the optimal hedge ratio is demonstrated to show the applicability of the index.
